This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with image segmentation using the Watershed algorithm. It also involves semi-supervised learning, which could place it in the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The use of Kirchhoff's matrix tree theorem suggests that it could also belong to the data structures (cs.DS) sub-category. The paper involves graph theory, which could place it in the graph theory (cs.GR) sub-category. Finally, the use of effective resistance suggests that it could also belong to the numerical analysis (cs.NA) sub-category.
